5:
An inspector from the imperial court
is coming to investigate?
9:
Put simply, they're making sure the
Diviners' Commission isn't secretly
plotting against its superiors.
12:
Normally this wouldn't be an issue,
but the inspector this time is a bit of
a troublesome one.
14:
She insists on speaking with the
special guests of the Diviners'
Commission.
19:
Are you saying the shogunate is on
to us?
23:
With the exception of the spirit
hunters, the imperial court knows
the diviners are in league with many
otherworldly organizations.
27:
However, their limited minds could
never imagine we would align
ourselves with a group as absurd as
yours.
31:
But this troublesome investigator of
theirs is a different story, isn't she?
35:
Indeed, which is why I believe it
prudent that we make the first move.
37:
It should be no challenge for you,
Alk. Simply reveal the cards in your
hand like usual, and the rest will
follow.
49: ...Are you the one they call Mayuzuki?
53:
My, my. And here I thought myself
thoroughly hidden. Excellent work.
57:
You even know my name. After all
that effort I went through to change
my appearance and obtain a new
moniker... That little rascal.
61:
Yes, I am Mayuzuki—Mayuzuki the
Unseen, but I suppose not today. I
serve as one of the shogunate's
spies.
68:
Of course. People who deal with
yokai and travel between worlds.
The diviners have even allied with
you.
71:
What I didn't expect was you to
know about me. You leave me no
choice...
85:
Do I need to spell it out for you? I'm a
spy, and I've been thoroughly
exposed.
87:
I'm worth nothing to my original
masters now, so I leave all that I am
to you. Use me however you like.
96:
I am but a tool. It makes no
difference to me who I'm wielded by.
103:
I hope you'll decide quickly. They're
already here to tie up loose ends.
106:
Mayuzuki! You were the best of us...
How could you let yourself be
ruined?!
111:
So what will it be? I'll slaughter them
all if you command it.
119:
Oh? Then I suppose I'll have to prove
my obedience another way.
122:
Hehehe, how about spending the
night together? I'll do whatever you
ask...
126: No thanks. I'll pass on that too.
131:
It's fun to mess with Alk, ain't it? Can't
blame you for playing around.
134:
But I know when a deal sounds too
good to be true.
139:
There's no deal. I'm a ninja. A tool.
And I'm handing my reins over to
you—no more, no less.
149: What do you want to do, Mayuzuki?
153:
Hehe, you've got quite the
disconcerting gaze.
155:
What I want is to maintain the status
quo. There have been a few pests
buzzing around lately, you see.
158:
I've spent a long time spinning
threads and building up a web here.
160:
I'd hate for all that hard work to go
to waste, so I tracked down these
pests to get to their nest.
165:
You're hunting down the ninja who
are trying to start a civil war, aren't
you?
169:
The shogunate realizes that making
enemies of the commission—of
you—is pointless.
171:
Open conflict isn't good for my web
of spies either. So why don't we work
together?
176:
Not going to make us one of your
little puppets?
181:
Oh, that? I've already given up on
that.
184:
I hope this clears things up. I'll be in
your care from now on.
193:
Aren't you just the most precious
little thing. Thank you, Stella.
198:
Just make sure you don't kill those
people.
201:
Otherwise, there's no way we can
work together.
205:
Letting them live is the same as
sentencing them to death, you know.
208:
As long as we're not the ones doing
the sentencing.
216:
Very well. It's more fun to make
them dance on strings anyway.
224: I'll make you mine as well.
232:
Oh, I'm just having a bit of fun. Don't
worry about it.
241:
I'm not entirely certain what's going
on, but... Hang in there, Alk.
250:
I'm gonna need more than luck, I
think.
